skills.name: Analytical problem solving and decision making
skills.description:
Analyzing problems and providing solutions in a structured way involving all relevant stakeholders.
	Anticipating problem areas and associated risk levels.
	Analyzing multiple alternatives, risks and benefits for a range of potential solutions.

skills.name: Attracting, engaging and retaining talent
skills.description: Establishing systems and processes to attract, develop, engage, and retain talented individuals; creating a work environment where people can realize their full potential, thus allowing the organization to meet current and future business challenges. Initiating strategies to develop internal talent while balancing that effort with external hiring; Targeting challenging developmental assignments that build individual confidence and organizational capability; Taking an individual’s potential to learn into consideration instead of solely focusing on existing skills; Allocating sufficient resources to learning and development. Emphasizing retention – Establishing systems to retain talented individuals; addressing employees’ needs for career satisfaction and engagement (e.g., compensation & benefits, development opportunities, work environment). Creating a team culture – Creating purpose by convening people around common causes; Considering personal fit during the hiring stage; Investing in diversity (gender, age, nationality, ethnic, mindset or cultural differences).

skills.name: Balanced scorecard
skills.description: The Balanced Scorecard concept focuses on strategic and operational Key Performance Indicators (KPIs) reported on a quarterly basis.
